`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    MyCall();
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => MyCall());
}
```

**Key variants:**

- **Async tests** â†’ use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)`
- **`AllowDerivedTypes = true`** â†’ use `Assert.Throws<T>` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>` instead (matches derived exception types)
- **Setup code before the throw** â†’ keep setup outside the lambda; wrap only the throwing call

> **Tip:** MSTest v3.2+ had analyzer **MSTEST0006** that flags `[ExpectedException]` usage â€” you could have migrated incrementally before upgrading to v4.
